    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>A deluge of necromantic power desiccates your target’s life force.</em></p><p>Necromantic energy rapidly washes over a creature of your choice that you can see within range, draining moisture and vitality from it. The target must make a CON save. It takes 8d8 necrotic damage on a failed save or half damage on a successful one. This spell has no effect on Undead or Constructs.</p><p>If you target a Plant creature or a magical plant, it makes the save with disadvantage, and the spell deals maximum damage to it. If you target a nonmagical plant that isn’t a creature, such as a tree or shrub, it withers and dies.</p><p><em><strong>At Higher Rings.</strong></em> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 5th ring or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot beyond 4th ring.</p>",
      "source": {
        "fallback": "Black Flag Reference Document"
      },
      "short": "Necrotic to living creature."
